cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.PL

The paper deals with the characterization of complexity classes, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of a geometry of interaction and a group action suggests a connection to algebraic structures and discrete mathematics, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the introduction of a concrete model for computing algorithms points towards programming languages (cs.PL) as another possible sub-category.
